Ayala Corp., First Philippine, Metro: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-04T00:56:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/ayala-corp-first-philippine-metro-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.2 percent to
4,319.37.  Ayala Corp. (AC)  ,  Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  : The companies are among eight groups planning to bid for a
15 billion peso ($350 million) contract to operate two Metro
Manila railways, Philippine Daily Inquirer reported, citing
government documents. Secretary Jose de Jesus, head of the
Department of Transportation and Communications, the agency that
will conduct the bidding, couldn’t be reached in his office for
comment. Ayala fell 1.2 percent to 379.40 pesos. Metro Pacific
declined 1.1 percent to 3.60 pesos.  First Philippine Holdings Corp. (FPH)  : The stock’s 12-
month share-price estimate was cut to 96.26 pesos from 98.14
peso at Manila-based CitisecOnline.com Inc., George Ching, an
analyst, said in a phone interview. The stock’s “buy” rating
was maintained, he said. The stock fell 0.3 percent to 66.10
pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
